  <subsection xml:id="problems-curvature-torsion">
    <title>Full Descriptions of Curves in <m>\RR^3</m></title>
    <activity>
      <statement>
        <p>
          For this curve, calculate the speed, curvature, torsion.
          Also calculate the tangent vector, normal vector and
          binormal vector. 
          <me>
            \gamma(t) = (t \cos t, t \sin t, ht)
          </me>
          Interpret the curve using the three scalar. In particular,
          describe the long term behaviour of the curse. 
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          We follow the lengthy process of calculating speed,
          curvature, torsion, the tangent vector, the normal vector,
          and the binormal vector. 
          <md>
            <mrow>
              \gamma(t) \amp = (t^3, 1 - t^2, 1 + t^2) 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \gamma^\prime(t) \amp = (x^\prime(t), y^\prime(t),
              z^\prime(t)) = (3t^2, -2t, 2t) 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              v(t) = |\gamma^\prime(t)| \amp = \sqrt{x^\prime(t)^2 +
              y^\prime(t)^2 + z^\prime(t)^2 }
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
             \amp = \sqrt{ 9t^4 + 4t^2 + 4t^2} = t \sqrt{9t^2 + 4} 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              T(t) \amp = \frac{\gamma^\prime(t)}{|\gamma^\prime(t)|} =
              \frac{1}{t\sqrt{9t^2 + 4}} \left( 3t^2, -2t, 2t) =
              \left( \frac{3t}{\sqrt{9t^2+4}} 
              \frac{-2}{\sqrt{9t^2+4}} 
              \frac{2}{\sqrt{9t^2+4}} \right) 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              T^\prime(t) \amp = \left( \frac{12}{(9t^2 +
              4)^{\frac{3}{2}}, \frac{-18t}{(9t^2+4)^{\frac{3}{2}}},
              \frac{18t}{(9t^2+4)^{\frac{3}{2}}} \right) =
              \frac{1}{(9t^2+4)^{frac{3}{2}}} (12, -18t, 18t)
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              |T^\prime(t)| \amp = \frac{1}{(9t^2+4)^{\frac{3}{2}}} \sqrt{
              144 + 324t^2 + 324t^2} = \frac{1}{(9t^2+4)^{\frac{3}{2}}} \sqrt{
              144 + 648t^2} = 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \kappa(t) \amp = \frac{|T^\prime(t)|}{|\gamma^\prime(t)|} =
              \frac{\frac{1}{(9t^2+4)^{\frac{3}{2}}} \sqrt{ 144 +
              648t^2}}{\sqrt{ 9t^4 + 4t^2 + 4t^2} = t \sqrt{9t^2 + 4}}
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = \frac{144 + 648 t^2}{(9t^2+4)^2}
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              N(t) \amp = \frac{1}{\sqrt{144 + 648t^2} \left( 12, -18t,
              18t \right) = \left( \frac{12}{\sqrt{144 + 648t^2},
              \frac{-18}{\sqrt{144 + 648t^2}, \frac{-18}{\sqrt{144 +
              648t^2} \right)
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              B(t) \amp = T(t) \times N(t)
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \tau(t) \amp = - \frac{B^\prime(t)}{|\gamma^\prime(t)|}
              \cdot N(t)
            </mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </activity>
